<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-16T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="373" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.01/18: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-16T14:00:00-04:00">September 16, 1930—2
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>104. On Thursday, September 18, you will please inform the Foreign
                            Minister that you are instructed by the Government of the <pb facs="0467" n="387" xml:id="pg_387"/> United States to enter into
                            full diplomatic relations with the new Argentine Government, thus
                            constituting recognition thereof.</p>
                        <p>An announcement of this will be made here late Wednesday afternoon. Until
                            released here, the above should be treated as confidential. Similar
                            action will be taken as to Bolivia and Peru.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>